HEADWORD: Free will
<hw>Free will</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A will free from
improper coercion or restraint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To come thus was I not constrained, but did⟦br⟧
On my <qex>free will</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The power asserted of moral beings of willing or
choosing without the restraints of physical or absolute
necessity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>freewill</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>free-will</ent>⟦br⟧
